  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the perspective view and top view of a torsion pendulum that consists of a vertical wire connected to the center of a horizontal disk. Two radii are drawn with the angle between them labeled delta theta sub 0.\" src=\"/images/d1f4842496f5455781563be285830b2c.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A torsion pendulum consists of a uniform disk, which has a rotational inertia <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub D\"><math alttext=\"I sub D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mtext>D</mtext></msub></math></span></span> about its center, suspended from a wire, as shown in the figure. The wire exerts a torque <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"tau\"><math alttext=\"tau\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>τ</mi></math></span></span> that is proportional to the disk’s angular displacement <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta theta\"><math alttext=\"delta theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Δ</mtext><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> from equilibrium, with a constant of proportionality <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"k sub W equals the fraction tau over delta theta\"><math alttext=\"k sub W equals the fraction tau over delta theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>k</mi><mtext>W</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>τ</mi><mrow><mtext>Δ</mtext><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span>. When the disk is given an angular displacement <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta theta sub 0\"><math alttext=\"delta theta sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Δ</mtext><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> from equilibrium and then released, it will oscillate with a period that depends on</p>\n",
